{#
Optional page-level head include for an extension.

What this file is for:
- Add CSS or JS that should only load when this extension section is present
- Add third-party assets such as KaTeX, charts, syntax highlighting, etc.
- Keep extension-specific page tweaks out of the shared site template

How it is used:
- templates/daily.md.j2 includes this file once for each rendered section:
    {% include "extensions/" + sec.key + "/head.html.j2" ignore missing %}
- Because it is included from the daily page template, it receives the same
  render context as the page, including common values such as:
    sec
    date
    generated_at
    meta
    sections_ordered

Safe default:
- If your extension does not need any extra head assets, delete this file.

Minimal example:
  <style>
    .my-source-card { border-left: 4px solid #1565c0; }
  </style>

  <script>
  document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", () => {
    console.log("my_source assets loaded");
  });
  </script>
#}
